cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an approach for building self-adaptive software systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper utilizes Case-based Reasoning as an adaptation engine. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper addresses the challenges of managing the adaptation space and handling run-time uncertainty in self-adaptive software systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) may be relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed approach. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) may be relevant if the self-adaptive software system is designed to run on distributed or parallel computing systems.
